The paper deals with a coding problem in which a sender wants to broadcast a message to multiple receivers with prior side information. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a graph parameter and studies its properties, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses various models for optimal index codes, which can be related to social networks and communication networks, falling under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
